Q: FormData and checkboxes A: <p>I have similiar problem, checkbox value need to be true or false so I use method <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData/has" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><code>FormData.has()</code></a> to check if input name exist then set it.</p>
<p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false" data-console="true" data-babel="false" data-babel-preset-react="false" data-babel-preset-ts="false">
<div class="snippet-code">
<pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>form.addEventListener("submit", function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  const data = new FormData(form);

  if (data.has('checkbox_on'))
    data.set('checkbox_on', true);
  else
    data.append('checkbox_on', false);

  for (const [name, value] of data) {
    console.log(name, ":", value)
  }
})</code></pre>
<pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;form id="form"&gt;
  &lt;input name="normal" type="text" value='example' /&gt;
  &lt;input id="inpt" name="checkbox_on" type="checkbox" /&gt;
  &lt;label for="inpt"&gt;on&lt;/label&gt;
  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;button type="submit"&gt;submit&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</p>

Q: Dynamic form that has similar fields for each of the values of a dropdown A: <p>A form group exist even ther'e no input in html.
You can imagine a formArray that store e.g. {name:'',description:``}
We are going to create two functions:
datoToForm (that return the formArray) and formToData (that return an array of Translations).</p>
<p>More or less</p>
<pre><code>  language = 0; //declare a variable &quot;language&quot;

  //Use this variable auxiliar to get an array ['RO','EN','DE','FR']
  languages = Object.keys(TranslationLanguage).filter((v) =&gt; isNaN(Number(v)));

  formArray = this.dataToForm();  //the formArray

  dataToForm(data: ProductCategory | null = null) {
    const formArray: FormArray&lt;FormGroup&gt; = new FormArray(
      this.languages.map(
        (x) =&gt;
          new FormGroup({
            name: new FormControl(''),
            description: new FormControl(''),
          })
      )
    );

    //here you give value to the formArray

    data &amp;&amp;
      data.translations.forEach((x) =&gt; {
        const index = this.languages.findIndex((l) =&gt; l == x.value);
        if (index &gt;= 0) {
          if (x.translationType == TranslationType.ShortDescription)
            formArray.at(index).get('name')?.setValue(x.value);
          if (x.translationType == TranslationType.FullDescription)
            formArray.at(index).get('description')?.setValue(x.value);
        }
      });
    return formArray;
  }

  formToData(value:any[]) {
    const data: Translation[] = [];
    value.forEach((x, i: number) =&gt; {
      if (x.name) {
        data.push({
          id: '',
          translationType: TranslationType.ShortDescription,
          language: i as TranslationLanguage,
          value: x.name,
        });
      }
      if (x.description) {
        data.push({
          id: '',
          translationType: TranslationType.FullDescription,
          language: i as TranslationLanguage,
          value: x.description,
        });
      }
    });
  }


</code></pre>
<p>So, you can to have a html like</p>
<pre><code>&lt;select [(ngModel)]=&quot;language&quot;&gt;
@for (lang of languages;track $index)
{
   &lt;option [value]=&quot;$index&quot;&gt;{{lang}}&lt;/option&gt;
}
&lt;/select&gt;
@if (formArray.at(+language))
{
    &lt;form [formGroup]=&quot;formArray.at(+language)&quot;&gt;
        &lt;input formControlName=&quot;name&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;input formControlName=&quot;description&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/form&gt;
}

</code></pre>
<p>See that the &quot;key&quot; is the <code>[formGroup]=&quot;formArray.at(+language)&quot;</code></p>
